Hailing from the house of Timex and belonging to its highly popular series of analog watches for women is personal timepiece which manages to find the perfect balance between style and sophistication. Featuring the most essential function of timekeeping this casual women’s timepiece is sure to add considerable value to your style statement.

The timekeeping function on this watch works on the popular quartz crystal technology which uses small bar shaped crystals of quartz or silicon dioxide as it is otherwise referred to as. These quartz crystals work by generating an electrical charge which causes them to vibrate at a thousand times a second making them extremely stable resonators for accurate timekeeping. The biggest advantage of employing this quartz crystal technology is its operational simplicity and accuracy while the entire manufacturing process remains relatively cost effective.

Body and Design

Sporting an attractive rectangular dial this watch features a watch face that is largely dominated by a very light and solid coloured background. The only hour positions on the dial are the 12 3 6 and 9 o’clock which are marked with small yet clearly visible metal studs. The only other element on the dial is the watchmaker’s logo in a prominent dark colour which is located just below the 12-hour mark.

This intricately designed dial is surrounded by a sturdy case with a brilliant metallic finish which also helps notch up the watch’s aesthetic value. The watch’s three hands are given a similar colour and finish as the dial’s case. The hour and the minute hands sport a skeletal structure that resembles the outline of a leaf thus sticking to the floral theme of the watch. This metallic colour against the light background makes the process of reading the time immensely easy and hassle-free.

The watch’s dial and case configuration stays firmly and comfortably attached to your wrist with its posh genuine leather strap. All the necessary time adjustments can easily be done through the watch’s rotating crown which is found on the right side of the dial’s case. The combination of the sturdy case along with the dial’s clear glass cover gives the watch the capability to be water-resistant giving you a wristwatch that is visually captivating with a great deal of practicality.

This highly rated timepiece features an analog style display with the inclusion of a slightly less prominent digital display making it a crossover model with a perfect combination of highly useful technologies.

Built to reflect a certain rugged outdoor adventure feel this dual technology watch can be used across a multitude of places occasions and climatic conditions. As a unisex watch this T49826 from Timex is designed and styled to be worn by both men and women. This crossover design successfully combines all the fine elements of the great outdoors along with a sense of style and sophistication.

Body & Design

Particularly designed with great amount of importance given to the all-weather functionality of this highly complex timepiece the T49826 features a bold round dial and watch face. This all important dial is protected by a strong and sturdy resin casing that runs around the entire curve of the glass. This protective casing on the outside of the glass has very prominent markings of the key time positions which alternate starting from the 12 O’clock position all the way around.

This highly capable timepiece is fastened onto your wrist by a very classy and elegant IP Ruthenium Bracelet that matches the colour of the dial. This use of Ruthenium gives the watch amazing strength and a great heat resistance which proves extremely useful considering the outdoor applications of this Expedition series watches.

Multi-functionality being the key aspect of this watch this Timex T49826 features nothing less than 4 push buttons and a rotating crown which are neatly distributed around the protective fibre case. The rotating crown lets you change or set the correct time while the 4 push buttons are evenly distributed around the watch’s casing with 2 on the left and 2 on the right and are used to operate the alarm set mode and indiglo functionalities.

Functions & Other Features

Perfectly suited for outdoor activities like hiking camping trekking or just exploring this Timex Expedition combo watch provides you with the best of both worlds with its ability to flawlessly combine digital and analog functionalities into one super-efficient and multifunctional personal timekeeper. This Timex Expedition watch from Timex comes loaded with a considerable assortment of highly efficient and immensely useful functions including an analog/digital chronograph and a 24-hour countdown timer.

The analog and digital type displays on this Timex T49826 gives you the ability to read the time using the watch arms or using the digital display. The chronograph function on this watch further comes with an extremely accurate stopwatch with multiple split or lap time feature. This stopwatch with lap or split timers comes in immensely handy for those involved in any field where the accuracy of even the tiniest measure of time counts.

The digital display gives you the option to choose between the 12 and 24-hour time format according to whichever suits you best. This super-efficient and multifunctional timepiece from Timex further comes with the inclusion of an alarm clock function. The alarm can be set and be seen on the digital display that works using the standard beep alarm tone.

This T49826 from Timex has features a highly functional night mode that operates using Timex’s trademark INDIGLO lighting technology that illuminates both the analogue face and the digital display. The water-resistant feature on this watch gives it a maximum operational depth of 50 m which makes sure that water seepage or the subsurface pressure build-up doesn’t affect the watch’s normal functionality. In total this Timex Expedition watch makes an ideal buy giving you great aesthetics and practicality with an elevated degree of protection and reliability even against some of the highly unpredictable elements of nature.

If you are looking for an extremely trendy and fashionable sports accessory the designers from Timex may just have come up with the perfect product for you - their Ironman watch collection. Pictured here is the Timex Ironman Analog-digital Unisex Watch that is crafted for sports occasions. The time-keeping device keeps ticking in sync with your time zone thanks to the quartz mechanism.

Body and Design

Designed to be as comfortable as possible when you take part in your favourite sporting events on the field the Timex watch is fastened to your wrist with the help of a sturdy resin strap and a buckle clasp. The resin strap is also extremely durable against any potential abrasions that tend to occur when you play hard.

The appealing design of the Ironman analog-digital watch is complemented by its sturdy make. The contemporary dial is durable against wear and tear courtesy of a sturdy case made of stainless steel.

In addition the watch face of the timepiece from Timex is protected by a highly-effective mineral crystal glass window. The glass makes sure that scratches and shocks are the last thing that would find their way onto the aesthetically pleasing dial.

Functions and Other Features

The Timex wristwatch is a must-have accessory for sports-freaks. Equipped with a 100 hour chronograph the watch displays the lap and split times in large digits. Undoubtedly the Timex unisex watch is an ideal workout accessory.

Use the four alarm settings to wake up on time for your exercise daily. Use the top pusher to select either lap or split time mode. The on-the-fly recall of lap or split option lets you access the data of previous workouts. The designers of the unisex Timex wristwatch have equipped the device to be water-resistant up to a depth of 200 m that allows you to time your laps during your daily swimming practice.

You can even carry the watch along to a camping trip and check time in the dark using the Indiglo night light or even use the night mode feature. If you are a frequent traveler use the two time zone settings to keep track of the time in two different countries. In the end the Timex Ironman analog-digital wristwatch undoubtedly makes for a must-have addition to your collection of timepieces.
